The Pension Transitional Arrangement Directorate (PTAD) is set to commence the verification of pensioners of the defunct Bank of Agriculture (BoA) in the South-West Zone. In a series of tweets on its Twitter handle, the directorate stated that the exercise will be followed by a mop-up verification for other pensioners who missed previous verification exercises under the Defined Benefit Scheme (DBS) in the zone from Monday, May 16, to Friday, May 20, 2022. “The 5-day Verification Exercise will take place at POWA (Police Officers Wives Association) Complex, No1, Oduduwa Street, GRA, Ikeja Lagos. From 8.00am to 4.00pm daily. “Pensioners are required to bring the originals and photocopies of their career documents stamped and signed BVN with the picture, one month stamped and signed bank statement, NIN or any other valid I.D